data.title: Ether falls 20% in a week, and Ripple CEO slams SEC over XRP lawsuit: CNBC Crypto World

data.title: Bitcoin Slips Lower Amid Stock Market Sell-Off
data.text: It's been a choppy week of trading for bitcoin (BTC), as the Federal Reserve hiked interest rates again. "All About Bitcoin's" week-in-review panel looks at the news affecting bitcoin markets and the outlook for the biggest cryptocurrency by market cap.

data.title: Bitcoin Tests Almost 2-Year Lows
data.text: Bloomberg's Katie Greifeld joins Ed Ludlow to discuss why cryptocurrencies lingered near almost two-year lows as digital-asset investors sought a fresh catalyst with central bank rate increases depressing demand for riskier assets. -------- Like this video?

data.title: US Judge Ordered Tether to Produce Financial Records Showing Backing of USDT
data.text: A New York judge ordered Tether to produce financial records on the backing of USDT as part of a lawsuit that alleges Tether conspired to issue USDT to inflate the price of bitcoin (BTC). CoinDesk Global Policy & Regulation Managing Editor Nikhilesh De breaks down the details.
